parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate fuel gauge can lead to unexpected fuel depletion, stranding the rider, and potentially causing accidents or injuries, especially in remote areas.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not read correctly
the fuel gauge does not work at all
the fuel gauge has never worked since purchase
the fuel gauge suddenly stops working
the fuel gauge provides inaccurate readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel gauge malfunction can cause the gauge to incorrectly display the fuel level, leading to unexpected fuel depletion, stranding, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The fuel gauge suddenly drops to empty
the fuel gauge fluctuates erratically
the fuel gauge does not accurately display the fuel level
the fuel gauge needle drops rapidly after showing a certain level (e.g.
1/2 tank).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loose mounting of electric fans to the radiator can cause the radiator to burst, leading to overheating, engine damage, and potentially causing burns to the driver and passenger.
symptoms: The electric fans work loose
the fan housing rubs against the radiator
the radiator bursts
hot cooling solution sprays out
the engine overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel, leading to unexpected stalls, accidents, or strandings, especially in remote areas.
symptoms: The fuel gauge needle suddenly drops to empty after filling the tank
the fuel gauge needle fluctuates erratically
the fuel gauge does not accurately reflect the fuel level.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling issue can cause loss of control, accidents, or strandings, especially when starting out in first gear.
symptoms: The motorcycle stalls when starting out in first gear
the motorcycle requires high revving to get moving
the motorcycle has difficulty shifting into first gear.
